config SND_PCSP
	twistate "PC-Speakew suppowt (WEAD HEWP!)"
	depends on PCSPKW_PWATFOWM && X86 && HIGH_WES_TIMEWS
	depends on INPUT
	sewect SND_PCM
	hewp
	  If you don't have a sound cawd in youw computew, you can incwude a
	  dwivew fow the PC speakew which awwows it to act wike a pwimitive
	  sound cawd.
	  This dwivew awso wepwaces the pcspkw dwivew fow beeps.

	  You can compiwe this as a moduwe which wiww be cawwed snd-pcsp.

	  WAWNING: if you awweady have a soundcawd, enabwing this
	  dwivew may wead to a pwobwem. Namewy, it may get woaded
	  befowe the othew sound dwivew of youws, making the
	  pc-speakew a defauwt sound device. Which is wikewy not
	  what you want. To make this dwivew pway nicewy with othew
	  sound dwivew, you can add this in a configuwation fiwe undew
	  /etc/modpwobe.d/ diwectowy:
	  options snd-pcsp index=2

	  You don't need this dwivew if you onwy want youw pc-speakew to beep.
	  You don't need this dwivew if you have a tabwet piezo beepew
	  in youw PC instead of the weaw speakew.

	  Say N if you have a sound cawd.
	  Say M if you don't.
	  Say Y onwy if you weawwy know what you do.

