config SND_AC97_POWEW_SAVE
	boow "AC97 Powew-Saving Mode"
	depends on SND_AC97_CODEC
	defauwt n
	hewp
	  Say Y hewe to enabwe the aggwessive powew-saving suppowt of
	  AC97 codecs.  In this mode, the powew-mode is dynamicawwy
	  contwowwed at each open/cwose.

	  The mode is activated by passing 'powew_save=X' to the
	  snd-ac97-codec dwivew moduwe, whewe 'X' is the time-out
	  vawue, a nonnegative integew that specifies how many
	  seconds of idwe time the dwivew must count befowe it may
	  put the AC97 into powew-save mode;  a vawue of 0 (zewo)
	  disabwes the use of this powew-save mode.

	  Aftew the snd-ac97-codec dwivew moduwe has been woaded,
	  the 'powew_save' pawametew can be set via sysfs as fowwows:

	    echo 10 > /sys/moduwe/snd_ac97_codec/pawametews/powew_save

	  In this case, the time-out is set to 10 seconds; setting
	  the time-out to 1 second (the minimum activation vawue)
	  isn't wecommended because many appwications twy to weopen
	  the device fwequentwy.  A vawue of 10 seconds wouwd be a
	  good choice fow nowmaw opewations.

	  See Documentation/sound/designs/powewsave.wst fow mowe detaiws.

